analysis: The agent failed to call the MediaDesignOptimizer_createVisualContent function to generate the requested Instagram content, addressing only the trend analysis task and neglecting the visual content creation requirement specified in the user's query.

The agent failed to call the function for all required combinations; it omitted Random Forest with 3 months and Neural Network with 1 month predictions, issuing only two instead of the expected four calls.

The agent incorrectly set the licenseManager calls' timeFrame to a single day (2025-10-09) instead of the full year (2025-01-01 to 2025-12-31) as requested, causing a parameter mismatch with the expected function calls.

The failure occurred because the model used "arguments" instead of "parameters" as the key in the function call payloads, resulting in a schema mismatch and no function call being recognized by the evaluator.

The agent only attempted the Escher artwork comparison and neglected to initiate the required creative writing session. Additionally, the tool call for Escher_Shape_Diff_Analyzer had malformed JSON, missing a closing brace, leading to parsing failure.

The agent incorrectly used the time period 2011-2020 for analyzing "Inception" instead of restricting the analysis to the film's actual year, 2010, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call parameters.

The agent incorrectly included a "severity" field in the "weather_conditions" parameters, which is not part of the expected function signature. This mismatch caused the function calls to not match the required schema, leading to evaluation failure.

The agent failed to call the document_management_store function to save the requested curriculum document, only generating the adaptive curriculum. It ignored the user's explicit instruction to store the document with specific metadata and sharing options.

The agent included non-empty feedbackData arrays in the MarketingCampaign_manageFeedback call, despite the instruction only to generate a report (not add new feedback). The expected output required empty feedbackData arrays for each source, but the agent added specific feedback entries.
The agent omitted the required "intensity": "High" parameter in the checkParameters for each function call, resulting in non-matching calls and failure to meet the expected input specification.

The agent incorrectly set the "from" date as "2026-11-01" instead of using the start of the year ("2026-01-01") for the cybersecurity threat evaluation, resulting in the function call not matching the expected parameters.

The agent output "United States" instead of the required "USA" for the country in the urban_air_quality_monitor call, resulting in a parameter mismatch and causing the evaluator to reject the function call as non-matching.

The agent incorrectly specified "cardboard boxes" as the packaging material instead of "cardboard," causing a mismatch with the expected function call parameters for FruitSorter_processSortedFruits. This led to the function call not being recognized as correct.

The model incorrectly included extraneous document_id fields in the insurance_claim_verification function call arguments, violating the expected schema which only required document_type for each document; this mismatch caused the evaluator to reject the function call as invalid.

The agent incorrectly included an "interactions": false key in the "details" argument, which is not part of the expected function call schema. This mismatch caused the evaluator not to recognize the function calls as valid.

The agent incorrectly assigned a severity of 5 to the "swelling" symptom instead of the expected severity of 3, resulting in a parameter mismatch for the ReptileBiteResponseSystem_evaluateBiteSeverity function call. All other aspects matched expectations.

The agent made only one function call and used the wrong tool (CinemaPhilosophyAnalyzer_analyzePhilosophicalThemes) instead of the required two: searching for purpose-driven films and performing a detailed existential analysis with the correct tool.

The agent omitted the required "documentTypes" parameter (with value ["passport"]) in its VisaInformationManager_getVisaRequirements function call, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call signature.

The agent's function calls omitted the required "event_details" field in the arguments, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function signature and causing the evaluator to not recognize the calls as valid.

The agent combined all vehicles into a single function call without including the required infrastructureResponse details per vehicle, instead of issuing separate, detailed calls for each car as specified by the task.

The agent incorrectly added "terms" parameters to the RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation function calls, which were not expected or required. This caused the function calls not to match the specification, resulting in failure.

The agent added an extra "terms" field to the RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation call that was not required, and omitted the "date" parameter from the RealEstateAdvisor_getMortgageDetails function, leading to mismatched function signatures and evaluation failure.

The agent failed to distinguish the two parallel resistors in the second circuit, using generic names ("resistor") instead of unique identifiers ("resistor1", "resistor2") in both components and connections, resulting in mismatched function call arguments.

The agent outputted the correct function calls and arguments, but used "arguments" instead of "parameters" as the key in the function call objects, resulting in a schema mismatch and failure to match the expected function calls.

The agent incorrectly included an empty "contact_number" field in each applicant_details object, which is not part of the required function schema. This causes the function calls to not match the expected parameters, resulting in evaluation failure.

The agent incorrectly set the "reverb" effect's intensity parameter to 0.9 instead of the expected maximum value of 1, and included an extra "apply_time": "real-time" parameter not required by the function, leading to a non-matching function call.

The agent failed to correctly infer and include the required "timeOfDay" parameters for both function calls ("afternoon" for audio and "12:01-18:00" for cooling system), instead using "night" and omitting it entirely, leading to mismatched function call signatures.

The agent incorrectly formatted the "settings" argument for the HomeLightingControl_manageLightSettings function as a list instead of an object, causing a mismatch with the expected function schema and preventing proper recognition by the evaluator.

The agent structured the "reason.details" field as an object with "scenario" and "examples" properties, instead of an array of objects containing only the "scenario" as required by the function schema, leading to a mismatch in the expected function call format.

The agent incorrectly combined both countries into a single function call using a list, instead of making separate function calls for each country as required by the function's expected parameter format.

The agent omitted the required includeEvents parameter (set to false) for the Colosseum. As a result, the function call did not exactly match the expected parameters, causing the evaluator to reject it.

The agent mismatched the capitalization of the "disputeNature" parameter ("property division" instead of "Property division") in the InheritanceMediationScheduler_scheduleSession function call, causing it not to match the expected function call signature and resulting in a failed test.
